 to report suspected abuse. After each section of material you will answer questions about that section\'s topic. This course must be completed to earn the \'Trained\' emblem. Estimated time to complete: 40 minutes.','Youth Protection','',1,'https://myscouting.scouting.org/Pages/eLearning.aspx'),(338,'T','Fast Start Orientation Training should be taken by pack, troop, team and crew leaders as well as ScoutParent unit coordinators, unit commissioners and chartered organization reps immediately following the acceptance of their new role. This training is offered online. Estimated time to complete: 45 minutes.','Fast Start','',2,'https://myscouting.scouting.org/Pages/eLearning.aspx'),(339,'T','Basic training is usually conducted at the district level. Check your districts website or attend Round Table for more information.','Basic','',3,'http://www.scouting.org/Training/Adult.aspx'),(340,'T','Hazardous Weather training must be completed prior to requesting a tour permit from the BSA. It presents safety precautions for 8 different types of weather as well as planning preparation and traditional weather signs. Estimated time to complete: 40 minutes.','Hazardous Weather','',4,'https://myscouting.scouting.org/Pages/eLearning.aspx'),(341,'T','All swimming activities in Scouting are required to follow the eight basic principles known collectively as the Safe Swim Defense plan. A unit that follows the plan can expect a safe enjoyable aquatic experience. Safe Swim Defense is required for BSA tour permits.','Safe Swim Defense','',5,'https://myscouting.scouting.org/Pages/eLearning.aspx'),(342,'T','All boating activities in Scouting are required to follow the nine basic principles of Safety Afloat. With an emphasis on accident prevention through proper preparation and skills a unit that follows Safety Afloat can expect a safe enjoyable activity. Safety Afloat is required for BSA tour permits for any trip afloat.','Safety Afloat (Boating)','',6,'https://myscouting.scouting.org/Pages/eLearning.aspx'),(343,'T','Climb On Safely is the  BSA\'s required procedure for organizing \nunit climbing and rappelling activities at all levels of the Scouting program. For council and district climbing and rappelling activities the current\nProject COPE and Climbing/Rappelling National Standards must be followed. \nClimb On Safely applies to climbing and rappelling at natural sites and specially \ndesigned facilities such as climbing towers and walls whether fixed or portable.','Climb On Safety','',7,'https://myscouting.scouting.org/Pages/eLearning.aspx'),(344,'T','Trek Safely is the  BSA\'s recommended procedure for organizing\nand carrying out outdoor treks that involve Boy Scouts Varsity Scouts and\nVenturers. Trek Safely applies to all types of outdoor experiences that involve\ntrekking including hiking, backpacking, canoeing, horseback riding, caving, \nrafting kayaking, sailing, ski touring, mountain climbing and mountain biking.','Trek Safely','',8,'https://myscouting.scouting.org/Pages/eLearning.aspx'),(345,'T','This is for all program areas and is an introductory session that highlights the values, aims, history, funding and methods of Scouting. It addresses how these aims and methods are reached in an age-appropriate style within Cub Scouting, Boy Scouting, Varsity Scouting and Venturing. Ideally all unit-based volunteers take this session at the same time so they understand that they are all striving for the same results with the youth they serve.','This is Scouting','',9,'https://myscouting.scouting.org/Pages/eLearning.aspx'),(346,'T','After the completion of Basic Leader Training adult volunteers involved with the Venturing or Boy Scout high adventure programs can take this course. Powder Horn is a new training opportunity designed as an action-packed hands on outdoor course to expose the Venturing and other Scouting adult leaders to the resources necessary to operate a successful unit-level high adventure program and support Venturing\'s Ranger Award program.','Powderhorn','',10,'http://www.scouting.org/Training/Adult.aspx'),(347,'T','Recommended within first two years of registration. \nOnce considered \'fully trained\' within a volunteers program leaders may participate. It is a comprehensive training course to help leaders hone skills, extend understanding and go on to new levels of personal growth and learning. Training time: Two full 3-day weekends (overnights) Prerequisite: Basic, This Is Scouting, Youth Protection, Specific Training for the position you are currently registered','Woodbadge','',11,'http://www.scouting.org/Training/adult.aspx'),(348,'T','This hands-on program gives adult leaders the practical outdoor skills they need to lead Scouts\r\nin the out-of-doors.','Outdoor Leader','',12,'http://www.scouting.org/Training/adult.aspx'),(349,'T','Scoutmaster Specific','Scoutmaster','',12,'http://www.scouting.org/Training/adult.aspx'),(499,'H','Faith in God','Faith in God','\0',0,NULL),(500,'C','Bobcat Badge','Bobcat','\0',1,NULL),(501,'C','Tiger Badge','Tiger Cub','\0',2,NULL),(502,'E','Tiger Cub Electives','Tiger Cub Electives','\0',1,NULL),(503,'C','Wolf Badge','Wolf','\0',3,NULL),(504,'E','Wolf Electives','Wolf Electives','\0',2,NULL),(505,'C','Bear Badge','Bear','\0',4,NULL),(506,'E','Bear Electives','Bear Electives','\0',3,NULL),(507,'C','Webelos Badge','Webelos Award','\0',5,NULL),(508,'C','Arrow Of Light','Arrow Of Light','\0',6,NULL),(510,'G','Aquanaut','Aquanaut','\0',1,NULL),(511,'G','Athlete','Athlete','\0',2,NULL),(512,'G','Fitness','Fitness','\0',3,NULL),(513,'G','Sportsman','Sportsman','\0',4,NULL),(514,'G','Artist','Artist','\0',5,NULL),(515,'G','Scholar','Scholar','\0',6,NULL),(516,'G','Showman','Showman','\0',7,NULL),(517,'G','Traveler','Traveler','\0',8,NULL),(518,'G','Citizen','Citizen','\0',9,NULL),(519,'G','Communicator','Communicator','\0',10,NULL),(520,'G','Family Member','Family Member','\0',11,NULL),(521,'G','Readyman','Readyman','\0',12,NULL),(522,'G','Craf