he four species. Discuss the habits and habitats of all 10 species.',104,''),(2573,'\0',2,'2. Discuss with your merit badge counselor the approximate number of species and general geographic distribution of reptiles and amphibians in the United States. Prepare a list of the most common species found in your local area or state.',104,''),(2574,'\0',3,'3. Describe the main differences between',104,''),(2575,'\0',4,'  a. Amphibians and reptiles ',104,''),(2576,'\0',5,'  b. Alligators and crocodiles ',104,''),(2577,'\0',6,'  c. Toads and frogs ',104,''),(2578,'\0',7,'  d. Salamanders and lizards ',104,''),(2579,'\0',8,'  e. Snakes and lizards ',104,''),(2580,'\0',9,'4. Explain how reptiles and amphibians are an important component of the natural environment. List four species that are officially protected by the federal government or by the state you live in, and tell why each is protected. List three species of reptiles and three species of amphibians found in your local area that are not protected. Discuss the food habits of all 10 species.',104,''),(2581,'\0',10,'5. Describe how reptiles and amphibians reproduce.',104,''),(2582,'\0',11,'6. From observation, describe how snakes move forward. Describe the functions of the muscles, ribs, and belly plates.',104,''),(2583,'\0',12,'7. Describe in detail six venomous snakes and the one venomous lizard found in the United States. Describe their habits and geographic range. Tell what you should do in case of a bite by a venomous species.',104,''),(2584,'\0',13,'8. Do ONE of the following:',104,'\0'),(2585,'\0',14,'  a. Maintain one or more reptiles or amphibians for at least a month. Record food accepted, eating methods, changes in coloration, shedding of skins, and general habits; or keep the eggs of a reptile from the time of laying until hatching; or keep the eggs of an amphibian from the time of laying until their transformation into tadpoles (frogs) or larvae (salamanders). ',104,''),(2586,'\0',15,'  b. Choo