loading rifle. ',105,''),(2636,'\0',45,'  h. Demonstrate the knowledge, skills, and attitude necessary to safely shoot a muzzle-loading rifle on a range, including range procedures. ',105,''),(2637,'\0',46,'  i. Shoot a target with a muzzle-loading rifle using the five fundamentals of firing the shot. ',105,''),(2638,'\0',47,'  j. Identify the materials needed to clean a muzzle- loading rifle safely. Using these materials, demonstrate how to clean a muzzle-loading rifle safely. ',105,''),(2639,'\0',48,'  k. Identify the causes of a muzzle-loading rifle\'s failing to fire and explain or demonstrate proper correction procedures. ',105,''),(2640,'\0',49,'  l. Discuss what points you would consider in selecting a muzzle-loading rifle. ',105,''),(2641,'\0',50,'  m. Using a muzzle-loading rifle of any caliber and shooting from a bench rest or supported prone position, fire three groups (three shots per group) that can be covered by the base of a standard-size soft soft drink can. ',105,''),(2642,'\0',51,'  n. Center the group on the target and fire three groups (five shots per group). According to the target used, each shot in the group must meet the following minimum score: (1) at 25 yards using NRA A-23 or NMLRA 50-yard targets - 7; (2) at 50 yards using NRA A-25 or NMLRA 100 yard targets - 7.\n\n    * Note: It is not always practical to adjust the sights (i.e. when using a borrowed fixed-sight rifle). For requirement 2l, you may demonstrate your ability to use the shooting fundamentals by shooting five shot groups (five shots per group) in which all shots can be covered by or touch a quarter and then explain how to adjust the sights to zero the rifle. ',105,''),(2643,'\0',1,'1. Show that you know first aid for and how to prevent injuries or illnesses that could occur while rowing, including cold and heat reactions, dehydration, contusions, lacerations, and blisters.',106,''),(2644,'\0',2,'2. Do the following:',106,''),(2645,'\0',3,'  a. Identify the condition