lor.',648,''),(4236,'\0',24,'  b. Describe the process and safety methods of working around at least two of the specialized SAR teams you identified above.',648,''),(4237,'\0',25,'  c. Explain the differences between wilderness, urban, and water SARs.',648,''),(4238,'\0',26,'7. Discuss the Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) system, latitude, and longitude. Then do the following:',648,''),(4239,'\0',27,'  a. Using a 1:24,000 scale USGS topographic map, show that you can identify a location of your choice using UTM coordinates.',648,''),(4240,'\0',28,'  b. Using a 1:24,000 scale map, ask your counselor to give you a UTM coordinate on the map, then identify that location.',648,''),(4241,'\0',29,'  c. Show that you can identify your current location using the UTM coordinates on a Global Positioning System (GPS) unit and verify it on a 1:24,000 scale map.',648,''),(4242,'\0',30,'  d. Determine a hypothetical place last seen, and point out an area on your map that could be used for containment using natural or human-made boundaries.',648,''),(4243,'\0',31,'8. Choose a hypothetical scenario, either one presented in this merit badge pamphlet or one created by your counselor. Then do the following:',648,''),(4244,'\0',32,'  a. Complete an incident objectives form for this scenario.',648,''),(4245,'\0',33,'  b. Complete an Incident Action Plan (IAP) to address this scenario.',648,''),(4246,'\0',34,'  c. Discuss with your counselor the behavior of a lost person and how that would impact your incident action plan (for example, the differences between searching for a young child versus a teen).',648,''),(4247,'\0',35,'  d. After completing 8a-8c, discuss the hypothetical scenario with your counselor.',648,''),(4248,'\0',36,'9. Discuss with your counselor the terms hasty team and hasty search. Then do the following:',648,''),(4249,'\0',37,'  a. Plan and carry out a practice hasty search-either urban or wilderness-for your patrol or troop. Include the following elements in the search: clue awareness, evidence preservation, tracking the subject, and locating the subject using attraction or trail sweep.',648,''),(4250,'\0',38,'  b. When it\'s over, hold a team debriefing to discuss the hasty search. Discuss problems encountered, successful and unsuccessful tactics, and ideas for improvement.',648,''),(4251,'\0',39,'10. Find out about three career or volunteer opportunities in search and rescue. Pick one and find out the education, training, and experience required for this professional or volunteer position. Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this position might interest you.',648,''),(4252,'\0',6,'  Marksman I TQ-40 Standing 10  5  20',647,''),(4253,'\0',1,'Complete these three requirements:',625,''),(4254,'\0',0,'  ',NULL,''),(4255,'\0',0,'',NULL,''),(4256,'\0',0,'%%% Cub Scouting Religious Square Knot Patch - Below are the requirements for the LDS Church.  Requirements for other churches are determined by those churches, not by Boy Scouts.  For information about how to earn a Scout Religious Emblem for another faith, contact your church, your Cub or Boy Scout leader',499,'\0'),(4257,'\0',1,'1. Faith in God Award Requirements',499,''),(4258,'\0',2,'Basic Requirements An important part of faith in God is keeping your baptismal covenant and staying spiritually strong. To help you develop faith and resist temptation, do the following things:',499,'\0'),(4259,'\0',3,'  A. Pray daily to Heavenly Father.',499,''),(4260,'\0',4,'  B. Read the scriptures regularly.',499,''),(4261,'\0',5,'  C. Keep the commandments and live \'My Gospel Standards\' (see back cover).',499,''),(4262,'\0',6,'  D. Honor your parents and be kind to your family.',499,''),(4263,'\0',7,'  E. Pay your tithing and attend tithing settlement.',499,''),(4264,'\0',8,'  F. Attend sacrament meetings and Primary regularly.',499,''),(4265,'\0',9,'Other Requirements: Doing the following activities will help your understanding and testimony of t