we faithfully live the Word of Wisdom. Help plan and conduct an activity to teach the Word of Wisdom to others.',499,''),(4283,'\0',27,'  H. Prepare a pedigree chart with your name and your parents\' and grandparents\' names. Prepare a family group record for your family and share a family story. Discuss how performing temple work blesses families.%%%',499,''),(4284,'\0',28,'  I. Learn to sing \'Choose the Right\' (Hymns,no. 239). Explain what agency is and what it means to be responsible for your choices. Discuss how making good choices has helped you develop greater faith.',499,''),(4285,'\0',29,'  J. Plan and complete your own activity that will help you learn and live the gospel (write the activity below).',499,''),(4286,'\0',30,'3. Serving Others',499,''),(4287,'\0',31,'And behold, I tell you these things that ye may learn wisdom; that ye may learn that when ye are in the service of your fellow beings ye are only in the service of your God. Mosiah 2:17\r\n    Complete at least two of the following activities each year:',499,'\0'),(4288,'\0',32,'  A. Read and discuss the parable of the good Samaritan (see Luke 10:30-37). Plan and complete a service project that helps a family member or neighbor. After completing the project, discuss how it helped your faith grow stronger.',499,''),(4289,'\0',33,'  B. Write a letter to a teacher, your parents, or your grandparents telling them what you appreciate and respect about them.%%%',499,''),(4290,'\0',34,'  C. Make a list of the qualities you like in a person. Choose one quality to develop in yourself. Discuss how showing respect and kindness strengthens you, your family, and others.',499,''),(4291,'\0',35,'  D. Plan, prepare, and serve a nutritious meal.',499,''),(4292,'\0',36,'  E. Entertain young children with songs or games you have learned or made yourself. Show that you know how to care for and protect a young child.',499,''),(4293,'\0',37,'  F. Learn about and practice good manners and courtesy.',499,''),(4294,'\0',38,'  G. Plan and hold a parent-child activity, such as a dinner, picnic, hike, day trip, or service project.',499,''),(4295,'\0',39,'   H. Read the twelfth article of faith. Discuss what it means to be a good citizen and how your actions can affect others. %%%  <b>(Note: The second square knot icon on page 9 in the book has been omitted and replaced by this one.)</b>',499,''),(4296,'\0',41,'  I. Plan and complete your own activity to serve others.',499,''),(4297,'\0',42,'4. Developing Talents',499,''),(4298,'\0',43,'For all have not every gift given unto them; for there are many gifts, and to every man is given a gift by the Spirit of God. Doctrine and Covenants 46:11\r\n    Complete at least two of the following activities each year:',499,'\0'),(4299,'\0',44,'  A. Learn how to budget and save money. Discuss why it is important to faithfully pay our tithing and how Heavenly Father blesses us when we do (see 3 Nephi 24:10-11). Pay your tithing and begin saving for a mission.',499,''),(4300,'\0',45,'  B. Learn to sing, play, or lead a song from the Children\'s Songbook. Teach or share the song in a family home evening or at Primary. Discuss how developing talents helps prepare us for service to Heavenly Father and others.',499,''),(4301,'\0',46,'  C. Write a poem, story, or short play that teaches a principle of the gospel or is about Heavenly Father\'s creations.%%%',499,''),(4302,'\0',47,'  D. Make an item from wood, metal, fabric, or other material, or draw, paint, or sculpt a piece of art. Display your finished work for others to see.',499,''),(4303,'\0',48,'  E. Visit an art museum or attend a concert, play, or other cultural event. Share your experience with your family or activity day group.',499,''),(4304,'\0',49,'  F. Read D&C 88:118. Discuss what it means to \'seek learning, even by study and also by faith.\' Improve your personal study habits by doing such things as learning how to choose and read good books or being prepared for school each day.',499,''),(4305,'\0',50,'  G. List five things you can do to help around your home. Discuss the importance of obeying and honoring your parents and learning how to work.',499,''),(4306,'\0',51,'  H. Plan a physical fitness program for yourself that may include learning to play a sport or game. Participate in the program for one month.',499,''),(4307,'\0',52,'  I. Learn about and practice good nutrition, good health, and good grooming, including modest dress.',499,''),(4308,'\0',53,'  J. Plan and complete your own activity that will help you develop your talents (write the activity below).',499,''),(4309,'\0',54,'5. Preparing for the Priestood',499,''),(4310,'\0',55,'\'The Priesthood of Aaron ... is an appendage to the greater, or the Melchizedek Priesthood, and has power in administering outward ordinances.\' Doctrine and Covenants 107:13-14\r\n    Do the following activities while you are 11 years old. They will help you prepare to receive the Aaronic Priesthood and become a righteous young man.',499,'\0'),(4311,'\0',56,'  A. Learn about the restoration of the Aaronic Priesthood (see D&C 13, D&C 107:20, and Joseph Smith-History 1:68-73).',499,''),(4312,'\0',57,'  B. Read D&C 20:57-60 and Aaronic Priesthood: Fulfilling Our Duty to God [Deacon], page 7. Discuss with a parent or leader the purposes of the Aaronic Priesthood and what it means to do your duty to God.',499,''),(4313,'\0',58,'  C. Talk with the deacons quorum presidency about the role of the deacons quorum. Write in your journal how you can serve the Lord as a member of a deacons quorum.',499,''),(4314,'\0',59,'  D. Read D&C 88:77-80, 118 and D&C 130:19. Discuss with a parent or Primary leader how important a good education is and how it can help strengthen you as a priesthood holder in your home and family and in the Church.',499,''),(4315,'\0',60,'  E. Read \'The Family: A Proclamation to the World.\' Make a list of things you can do to help strengthen your family and make a happy home. Share the list with your parents or Primary leader.',499,''),(4316,'\0',61,'6. My Testimony',499,''),(4317,'\0',62,'As you learn and live the gospel, your testimony will continue to grow. Use these pages to write your testimony about Heavenly Father and the Savior. Also write what the baptismal covenant means to you. You may also want to add to your written testimony in your personal journal.',499,''),(4318,'\0',63,'7. The Articles of Faith',499,''),(4319,'\0',64,'Complete all of the following:',499,'\0'),(4320,'\0',65,'  1. WE BELIEVE in God, the Eternal Father, and in His Son, Jesus Christ, and in the Holy Ghost.',499,''),(4321,'\0',66,'  2. WE BELIEVEthat men will be punished for their own sins, and not for Adam\'s transgression.',499,''),(4322,'\0',67,'  3. WE BELIEVEthat through the Atonement of Christ, all mankind may be saved, by obedience to the laws and ordinances of the Gospel.',499,''),(4323,'\0',68,'  4. WE BELIEVEthat the first principles and ordinances of the Gospel are: first, Faith in the Lord Jesus Christ; second, Repentance; third, Baptism by immersion for the remission of sins; fourth, Laying on of hands for the gift of the Holy Ghost.',499,''),(4324,'\0',69,'  5. WE BELIEVEthat a man must be called of God, by prophecy, and by the laying on of hands by those who are in authority, to preach the Gospel and administer in the ordinances thereof.',499,''),(4325,'\0',70,'  6. WE BELIEVEin the same organization that existed in the Primitive Church, namely, apostles, prophets, pastors, teachers, evangelists, and so forth.',499,''),(4326,'\0',71,'  7. WE BELIEVEin the gift of tongues, prophecy, revelation, visions, healing, interpretation of tongues, and so forth.',499,''),(4327,'\0',72,'  8. WE BELIEVEthe Bible to be the word of God as far as it is translated correctly; we also believe the Book of Mormon to be the word of God.',499,''),(4328,'\0',73,'  9. WE BELIEVEall that God has revealed, all that He does now reveal, and we believe that He will yet reveal many great and important things pertaining to the Kingdom of God.',499,''),(4329,'\0',74,'  10. WE BELIEVEin the literal gathering of Israel and in the restoration of the Ten Tribes; that Zion (the New Jerusalem) will be built upon the American continent; that Christ will reign personally upon the earth; and, that the earth will be renewed and receive its paradisiacal glory.',499,''),(4330,'\0',75,'  11. WE CLAIM the privilege of worshiping Almighty God according to the dictates of our own conscience, and allow all men the same privilege, let them worship how, where, or what they may.',499,''),(4331,'\0',76,'  12. WE BELIEVEin being subject to kings, presidents, rulers, and magistrates, in obeying, honoring, and sustaining the law.',499,''),(4332,'\0',77,'  13. WE BELIEVEin being honest, true, chaste, benevolent, virtuous, and in doing good to all men; indeed, we may say that we follow the admonition of Paul-We believe all things, we hope all things, we have endured many things, and hope to be able to endure all things. If there is anything virtuous, lovely, or of good report or praiseworthy, we seek after these things.',499,''),(4333,'\0',78,'8. My Gospel Standards',499,''),(4334,'\0',79,'  A. I will follow Heavenly Father\'s plan for me.',499,''),(4335,'\0',80,'  B. I will remember my baptismal covenant and listen to the Holy Ghost.',499,''),(4336,'\0',81,'  C. I will choose the right. I know I can repent when I make a mistake.',499,''),(4337,'\0',82,'  D. I will be honest with Heavenly Father, others, and myself.',499,''),(4338,'\0',83,'  E. I will use the names of Heavenly Father and Jesus Christ reverently. I will not swear or use crude words.',499,''),(4339,'\0',84,'  F. I will do those things on the Sabbath that will help me feel close to Heavenly Father and Jesus Christ.',499,''),(4340,'\0',85,'  G. I will honor my parents and do my part to strengthen my family.',499,''),(4341,'\0',86,'  H. I will keep my mind and body sacred and pure, and I will not partake of things that are harmful to me.',499,''),(4342,'\0',87,'  I. I will dress modestly to show respect for Heavenly Father and myself.',499,''),(4343,'\0',88,'  J. I will only read and watch things that are pleasing to Heavenly Father.',499,''),(4344,'\0',89,'  K. I will only listen to music that is pleasing to Heavenly Father.',499,''),(4345,'\0',90,'  L. I will seek good friends and treat others kindly.',499,''),(4346,'\0',91,'  M. I will live now to be worthy to go to the temple and do my part to have an eternal family.',499,''),(4347,'\0',1,'1. Learn and say the CUB SCOUT PROMISE and complete the Honesty Character Connection.',500,''),(4348,'\0',2,'  a. Know: Discuss these questions with your family. What is a promise? What does it mean to \'keep your word?\' What does honesty mean? What does it mean to \'do your best?\'',500,''),(4349,'\0',3,'  b. Commit: Discuss these questions with your family. Why is a promise important? Why is it important for people to trust you when you give your word? When might it be difficult to keep your word? List examples.',500,''),(4350,'\0',4,'  c. Practice: Discuss with family members why it is important to be trustworthy and honest and how can you do your best to be honest when you are doing the activities in Cub Scouting.',500,''),(4351,'\0',5,'2. Say the LAW OF THE PACK. Tell what it means.',500,''),(4352,'\0',6,'3. Tell what WEBELOS means.',500,''),(4353,'\0',7,'4. Show the CUB SCOUT SIGN. Tell what it means\r\n  [Webelos: Make the CUB SCOUT SIGN. Tell what it means.]',500,''),(4354,'\0',8,'5. Show the CUB SCOUT HANDSHAKE. Tell what it means.',500,''),(4355,'\0',9,'6. Say the CUB SCOUT MOTTO. A motto is a guiding principle. \'Do Your Best\'',500,''),(4356,'\0',10,'7. Give the CUB SCOUT SALUTE. Tell what it means.',500,''),(4357,'\0',11,'8. With your parent or guardian, complete the exercises in the booklet\r\n  How to Protect Your Children from Child Abuse\r\n  [Tiger Cub: With your adult partner, complete \'A Bobcat Requirement\' in front of the Contents pages of this handbook.]\r\n  [Webelos: With your parent or guardian, complete the Bobcat Requirements section of \'How to Protect Your Children from Child Abuse: A Parents Guide\'). (The guide is a pull-out section that came in the front of the book.)]',500,''),(4358,'\0',0,'The Tiger Cub Scout program is for boys who have completed Kindergarten (or are age 7). After earning the Bobcat badge, a boy may earn the Tiger Cub badge by completing 15 achievements involving simple physical and mental skills.',501,'\0'),(4359,'\0',1,'To begin his path to the Tiger Cub Rank, a boy must do the following to earn the Tiger Cub Totem:',501,'\0'),(4360,'\0',2,'  a. Learn the Cub Scout Motto: Do Your Best',501,''),(4361,'\0',3,'  b. Learn the Cub Scout Sign',501,''),(4362,'\0',4,'  c. Learn the Cub Scout Salute',501,''),(4363,'\0',5,'1. Making My Family Special',501,'\0'),(4364,'\0',6,'  F. Family Activity - Think of one chore you can do with your adult partner. Complete it together. Character Connection: Responsibility',501,''),(4365,'\0',7,'  D. Den Activity - Make a family scrapbook',501,''),(4366,'\0',8,'  G. Go See It Activity - Go to a library, historical society, museum, old farm, or historical building, or visit an older person in your community. Discover how family life was the same and how it was different many years ago.',501,''),(4367,'\0',9,'2. Where I Live',501,'\0'),(4368,'\0',10,'  F. Family Activity - Look at a map of your community with your adult partner.',501,''),(4369,'\0',11,'  D. Den Activity - Practice the Pledge of Allegiance with your den, and participate in a den or pack flag ceremony. Character Connection: Citizenship',501,''),(4370,'\0',12,'  G. Go See It Activity - Visit a police station or a fire station. Ask someone who works there how he or she helps people in your community.',501,''),(4371,'\0',13,'3. Keeping Myself Healthy and Safe',501,'\0'),(4372,'\0',14,'  F. Family Activity. Do both of the following:',501,'\0'),(4373,'\0',15,'    a. With your family, plan a fire drill then practice it in your home.',501,''),(4374,'\0',16,'    b. With your adult partner, plan what to do if you became lost or separated from your family in a strange place.',501,''),(4375,'\0',17,'  D. Den Activity - Make a Food Guide Pyramid. (Character Connection: Health and Fitness)',501,''),(4376,'\0',18,'  G. Go See It Activity - Learn the rules of a game or sport. Then, go watch an amateur or professional game or sporting event.',501,''),(4377,'\0',19,'4. How I Tell It',501,'\0'),(4378,'\0',20,'  F. Family Activity - At a family meal, have each family member take turns telling the others one thing that happened to him or her that day. Remember to practice being a good listener while you wait for your turn to talk. (Character Connection: Respect)',501,''),(4379,'\0',21,'  D. Den Activity - Play (Tell It Like It Isn\'t)',501,''),(4380,'\0',22,'  G. Go See It Activity - Visit a television station, radio station, or newspaper office. Find out how people there communicate with others.',501,''),(4381,'\0',23,'5. Let\'s Go Outdoors - This achievement is also part of Cub Scouting\'s Leave No Trace Award.',501,'\0'),(4382,'\0',24,'  F. Family Activity - Go outside and watch the weather (Character Connection: Faith)',501,''),(4383,'\0',25,'  D. Den Activity - With a crayon or colored pencil and a piece of paper, make a leaf rubbing.',501,''),(4384,'\0',26,'  G. Go See It Activity - Take a hike with your den.',501,''),(4385,'\0',1,'After completing the fifteen Achievements required for the Tiger Cub Rank Badge, the Tiger Cub can be awarded Tiger Track Beads, which are YELLOW disks attached to the Totem. One bead is awarded for each group of TEN Electives the Tiger Cub completes. A boy can work on both Achievements and electives concurrently, but he can\'t receive Tiger Track beads until he has earned the Tiger Cub Badge.',502,'\0'),(4386,'\0',2,'1. Think of a time when your family celebrated something, and tell the den about it and how it made your feel.',502,''),(4387,'\0',3,'2. Make a decoration with your family or your den. Display it or give it to someone as a gift.',502,''),(4388,'\0',4,'3. With your family, play a card or board game, or put a jigsaw puzzle together.',502,''),(4389,'\0',5,'4. Make a frame for a family picture.',502,''),(4390,'\0',6,'5. Make a family mobile.',502,''),(4391,'\0',7,'6. Along with your adult partner, teach a song to your family or to your den and sing it together.',502,''),(4392,'\0',8,'7. Make a musical instrument and play it with others. The others can sing or have instruments of their own.',502,''),(4393,'\0',9,'8. Invite a religious leader from your place of worship to your home or to your den meeting.',502,''),(4394,'\0',10,'9. Help a new boy or girl get to know other people.',502,''),(4395,'\0',11,'10. Along with your adult partner, help an elderly or shut-in person with a chore.',502,''),(4396,'\0',12,'11. Help collect food, clothing or toys for needy families with your den or pack.',502,''),(4397,'\0',13,'12. Make at least two cards or decorations and take them to a hospital or long-term care facility.',502,''),(4398,'\0',14,'13. Using US pennies, nickels, dimes and quarters, choose the correct coins to make the following amounts:  15 cents, 50 cents, 29 cents, 60 cents, 35 cents, 59 cents.',502,''),(4399,'\0',15,'__',502,'\0'),(4400,'\0',16,'14. Together with your adult partner, read a short story or a magazine article.',502,''),(4401,'\0',17,'15. Mix the primary colors to make orange, green and purple.',502,''),(4402,'\0',18,'16. With your den, show or tell about something you like to collect, OR tell your den about a favorite hobby or activity.',502,''),(4403,'\0',19,'17. Make a model.',502,''),(4404,'\0',20,'18. Sew a button onto fabric.',502,''),(4405,'\0',21,'19. Learn a magic trick and show it to your family or den.',502,''),(4406,'\0',22,'