r \'Start a Collection.\'',503,''),(4483,'\0',46,'  b. Make a collection of anything you like. Start with 10 things. Put them together in a neat way.',503,''),(4484,'\0',47,'  c. Show and explain your collection to another person.',503,''),(4485,'\0',48,'7. YOUR LIVING WORLD (Page 74)\r\n     This achievement is also part of the Cub Scout World Conservation Award and Cub Scouting\'s Leave No Trace Award.',503,''),(4486,'\0',49,'  a. Complete the Character Connection for Respect.',503,''),(4487,'\0',50,'    - Know. Discuss these questions with your family: What things have people done to show a lack of respect to our world? Why is it important to respect our environment and natural resources? How can you show respect for your environment?',503,''),(4488,'\0',51,'    - Commit. Discuss with your family how you feel when you see places in your neighborhood that have lots of litter. Name one thing you can do to help the environment.',503,''),(4489,'\0',52,'    - Practice. Practice being respectful while doing the requirements for (Your Living World.)',503,''),(4490,'\0',53,'  b. Land, air and water can get dirty.  Discuss with your family ways this can happen.',503,''),(4491,'\0',54,'  c. It takes a lot of energy to make glass, cans, and paper products.  You can help save energy by collecting these items for use again.  Find out how recycling is done where you live.  Find out what items you can recycle.',503,''),(4492,'\0',55,'  d. With an adult, pick up litter in your neighborhood.  Wear gloves to protect your hands against germs and cuts from sharp objects.',503,''),(4493,'\0',56,'  e. With an adult, find three stories that tell how people are protecting our world. Read and discuss them together.',503,''),(4494,'\0',57,'  f. Besides recycling, there are other ways to save energy.  List three ways you can save energy, and do them.',503,''),(4495,'\0',58,'8. COOKING AND EATING (Page 78)',503,''),(4496,'\0',59,'  a. Study the Food Guide Pyramid.  Name some foods from each of the food groups shown in the pyramid.',503,''),(4497,'\0',60,'  b. Plan the meals you and your family should have for one day. List things your family should have from the food groups shown in the Food Group Pyramid.  At each meal, you should have foods from at least three food groups.',503,''),(4498,'\0',61,'  c. Help fix at least one meal for your family. Help set the table, cook the food, and wash the dishes.',503,''),(4499,'\0',62,'  d. Fix your own breakfast. Wash and put away the dishes.',503,''),(4500,'\0',63,'  e. With an adult, help to plan, prepare, and cook an outdoor meal.',503,''),(4501,'\0',64,'9. BE SAFE AT HOME AND ON THE STREET (Page 82)',503,''),(4502,'\0',65,'  a. Complete the Character Connection for Responsibility.',503,''),(4503,'\0',66,'    - Know. Discuss these questions with your family: How does being responsible help us be safe? Within the past week, how did you show responsibility?',503,''),(4504,'\0',67,'    - Commit. Discuss these questions with your family: What happens when people are not responsible? What things can make you forget to be responsible? What things will help you be more responsible?',503,''),(4505,'\0',68,'    - Practice. Practice being responsible while doing the requirements for (Be Safe at Home and on the Street.)',503,''),(4506,'\0',69,'  b. WITH AN ADULT, check your home for hazards and know how to make your home safe.',503,''),(4507,'\0',70,'  c. WITH AN ADULT, check your home for danger from fire.',503,''),(4508,'\0',71,'  d. Practice good rules of street and road safety.',503,''),(4509,'\0',72,'  e. Know the rules of bike safety.',503,''),(4510,'\0',73,'10. FAMILY FUN (Page 88)\r\n     Do requirement a and do TWO of requirements 10b through 10g:',503,''),(4511,'\0',74,'  a. Complete the Character Connection for Cooperation.',503,''),(4512,'\0',75,'    - Know. Discuss these questions with your family: What is \'cooperation\'? Why do people need to cooperate when they are doing th