ory) and write a one sentence explanation for each.',506,''),(4945,'\0',68,'  d. Take a picture in your house.',506,''),(4946,'\0',69,'     -With available light.',506,''),(4947,'\0',70,'     -Using a flash attachment or photoflood (bright light).',506,''),(4948,'\0',71,'12. NATURE CRAFTS (Page 226)\r\n   This elective is also part of the Cub Scout World Conservation Award.',506,'\0'),(4949,'\0',72,'  a. Make solar prints of three kinds of leaves.',506,''),(4950,'\0',73,'  b. Make a display of eight different animal tracks with an eraser print.',506,''),(4951,'\0',74,'  c. Collect, press, and label ten kinds of leaves.',506,''),(4952,'\0',75,'  d. Build a waterscope and identify five types of water life.',506,''),(4953,'\0',76,'  e. Collect eight kinds of plant seeds and label them.',506,''),(4954,'\0',77,'  f. Collect, mount, and label ten kinds of rocks or minerals.',506,''),(4955,'\0',78,'  g. Collect, mount, and label five kinds of shells.',506,''),(4956,'\0',79,'  h. Build and use a bird caller',506,''),(4957,'\0',80,'13. MAGIC (Page 230)',506,'\0'),(4958,'\0',81,'  a. Learn and show three magic tricks.',506,''),(4959,'\0',82,'  b. With your den, put on a magic show for someone else.',506,''),(4960,'\0',83,'  c. Learn and show four puzzles.',506,''),(4961,'\0',84,'  d. Learn and show three rope tricks.',506,''),(4962,'\0',85,'14. LANDSCAPING (Page 236)',506,'\0'),(4963,'\0',86,'  a. With an adult, help take care of your lawn or flower beds or help take care of the lawn or flower beds of a public building, school, or church. Seed bare spots. Get rid of weeds. Pick up litter. Agree ahead of time on what you will do.',506,''),(4964,'\0',87,'  b. Make a sketch of a landscape plan for the area right around your home. Talk it over with a parent or den leader. Show which trees, shrubs and flowers you could plant to make the area look better.',506,''),(4965,'\0',88,'  c. Take part in a project with your family, den, or pack to make your neighborhood o