 observe kashrut while camping.',221,''),(8570,'\0',20,'    b. What reason does the Torah give for the observance of kashrut?',221,''),(8571,'\0',23,'Do the first requirement and complete one of the other three.',221,''),(8572,'\0',22,'2. SYNAGOGUE WORSHIP--Living the Jewish Life in the Synagogue',221,'\0'),(8573,'\0',17,'  3 a. Give the titles of at least five Jewish books that every Jewish home should have. Include books for study, prayer, and reading.',221,''),(8574,'\0',16,'    c. Give the Hebrew dates of the High Holy Days and festivals.',221,''),(8575,'\0',19,'  4 a. Read and explain the following verses in the Bible, which contain some of the sources for the observance of kashrut: Leviticus 11; Deuteronomy 12:16, 23; Genesis 32:33; Exodus 23:19, 34:26; and Deuteronomy 14:21.',221,''),(8576,'\0',18,'    b. Read a book of Jewish interest approved by your rabbi or counselor and write a book report of at least 200 words.',221,''),(8577,'\0',41,'  2. Give a presentation of what you have learned about your Jewish community to at least two groups. At least one should be to a group of younger Jewish children. Use your record in your presentation.',222,''),(8578,'\0',29,'  3 a. Show evidence that you are Bar Mitzvah or that you will be Bar Mitzvah.',221,''),(8579,'\0',28,'    b. Write a brief composition (about 200 words) on the subject “How the Ner Tamid program helps a Scout put into practice a Scout is reverent.”',221,''),(8580,'\0',39,'7. Community Sharing',222,'\0'),(8581,'\0',31,'    c. Explain the meaning and contents of the tefilin and learn how and when they are used.',221,''),(8582,'\0',40,'  1. Create a record of your work for the Etz Chaim religious emblem. This may be a photographic essay, a videotape recording, a series of drawings, or a written journal.',222,''),(8583,'\0',30,'    b. Chant or read the blessings on being called to the Torah for an aliyah.',221,''),(8584,'\0',25,'    b. Describe and explain the use of some of the sacred ceremonial objects such as Ner Tamid, Sefer Torah, Aron Kodesh, etrog and lulav, shofar, and Megilah.',221,''),(8585,'\0',24,'  1 a. Attend synagogue Sabbath services regularly.',221,''),(8586,'\0',27,'  2 a. Give the important ideas contained in the kiddush, Shema, Amidah, Alenu, En Kelohenu, Yigdal, and two other prayers.',221,''),(8587,'\0',26,'    c. What Jewish activities, other than worship, are sponsored by or conducted in your synagogue?',221,''),(8588,'\0',34,'  3. Locate, read, and summarize two articles dealing with the concerns of Jewish people outside the United States. For example, in Israel, Canada, Europe, etc.',222,''),(8590,'\0',33,'  2. Locate, read, and summarize two articles dealing with the concerns of Jewish people in the United States.',222,''),(8592,'\0',32,'  1. Obtain a copy of a Jewish newspaper that serves your community or region.',222,''),(8594,'\0',31,'5. Your Community and the Jewish World ',222,'\0'),(8596,'\0',38,'  2. Locate and read an article from a national Jewish magazine about Jewish people and the future. Tell how the topic discussed in the article might affect your Jewish community.',222,''),(8597,'\0',37,'  1. Ask ten Jewish young adults and ten Jewish adults what they think are the three most important challenges that Jewish people face in your community today. Organize the responses into three lists: personal issues, family issues, and community issues. Select one issue from each list and tell what you think should be done to deal with it.',222,''),(8598,'\0',1,'The Ner Tamid emblem is a pendant representing the Eternal Light that hangs in front of the Holy Ark in the synagogue. It is attached to a blue and white ribbon and a bronze bar pin that carries the inscription \"Ner Tamid\" in Hebrew letters and \"Eternal Light\" in English.\nThe Ner Tamid in the synagogue of our own day goes back to the seven-branched menorah described in the Bible (Exodus 27:20; Numbers 8:2). The center light, from which the other six were kindled, is the Ner Tamid. The lamp burned continually, symbolizing the Jewish people\'s eternal devotion to God\'s teachings. For more information visit http://www.jewishscouting.org/ner-tamid-religious-emblem/',221,'\0'),(8599,'\0',36,'6. Your Community and the Future',222,'\0'),(8601,'\0',35,'  4. Ask three Jewish adults you know what they do to help Jewish people outside the United States, and why. Tell which effort interests you most.',222,''),(8603,'\0',26,'  3. What were the Jewish influences in the leader’s life while growing up?',222,''),(8604,'\0',12,'  1 a. Tell how the Sabbath should be observed and the meaning of this observance.',221,''),(8605,'\0',25,'  2. Why did the leader enter his or her chosen career or occupation?',222,''),(8606,'\0',13,'    b.Tell how the following High Holy Days and festivals are celebrated and the meaning of these observances to you: Rosh Hashana, Yom Kippur, Sukkot, Pesach, Shavuot, Chanukah, Purim, and Tishah b’Av.',221,''),(8607,'\0',24,'  1. Interview five adult Jewish leaders who are prominent in your community. Choose at least one rabbi and one leader from a Jewish agency or organization.',222,''),(8608,'\0',14,'  2 a. Study a Hebrew calendar (luach) and tell how it differs from the general calendar.',221,''),(8609,'\0',23,'4. Community Jewish Leaders ',222,'\0'),(8610,'\0',15,'    b. Give the names of the Hebrew months.',221,''),(8611,'\0',30,'  7. Write a short composition (five hundred words) titled “The Qualities of Adult Jewish Leadership Today.”',222,''),(8613,'\0',29,'  6. What role does faith in God play in your life as a Jew?',222,''),(8615,'\0',28,'  5. How do Judaism and Jewish values influence his or her life today?',222,''),(8616,'\0',10,'1. HOME OBSERVANCE--Living the Jewish Life at Home',221,'\0'),(8617,'\0',27,'  4. What volunteer work does the leader do now and why?',222,''),(8618,'\0',11,'Do the first requirement and choose one of the other three.',221,'');
